Borussia Dortmund winger, Jadon Sancho, has chosen to play for Manchester United. According to the Daily Mail, the England international wants to leave Dortmund in the summer transfer window later this year, and Man United is his number one choice. DAILY POST had reported that Man United alongside Liverpool and Chelsea are also interested in signing Sancho. Dortmund could demand as much as £100million for Sancho, who has been impressive for the Bundesliga giants so far this season. Sancho joined Dortmund from Pep Guardiola’s Manchester City in 2017. The 19-year-old has scored 29 goals in 84 appearances for the since joining Dortmund. He came in second position behind Atletico Madrid star, Joao Felix, for last 2019’s Golden Boy award for the best under-21 players in Europe. 